ŞMICHAEL JOHN COULING
1942 - 2001
SITTING HERE I SEE OUR MEMORIES, FLOW IN ON THE TIDE
HEAR YOUR VOICE IN THE GULLS CRY
FEEL YOUR TOUCH ON THE BREEZE
SUSAN SMALLWOOD
WHO LOVED YOU"╠
╔[Top Left]
Auntie Myrtle
Myrtle Masters who died
February 1995 aged 100
Lovingly remembered by
Julian, Audrey, Mark,
May and Charles

[Top Right]
Auntie Winnie
Winifred Becket who died
July 1983 aged 83
Lovingly remembered by
Julian, Audrey, Mark,
Army and Archie

[Bottom]
JULIAN HENWOOD
a Padstonian who died 13th January 2013
Gone are the days we used to share
but in our hearts you will always be there.
Audrey, Mark, Sophie and JJ."╬
╦[Left]
With fond memories of
MARTIN COOK
His guitar is silent 
His fingers no longer work
Those days have slipped away
All the hours that he played
Just a man who played his guitar.

[Center]
WITH HAPPY MEMORIES
JOYCE AND GERALD (GUS) STEELS
OF LOUGHTON, ESSEX
WHO LOVED PADSTOW AND
REGARDED IT AS THEIR SECOND HOME

[RIGHT]
In loving memory of
JOHN and EILEEN PEARCE
from Epsom, Surrey
who spent so many happy times
in and around Padstow"Ń
